        <div class="section-header">
          <h2>Shopping</h2>
          <p>From the historic Market Square to independent boutiques, Newark has a shopping scene to suit every taste.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid--3">
          <div class="info-card">
            <h3>Newark Market</h3>
            <p>One of the largest traditional markets in the East Midlands. Fresh produce, clothing, household goods, and street food spread across the magnificent cobbled Market Square on Monday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday and Saturday.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="info-card">
            <h3>The Buttermarket</h3>
            <p>A covered shopping area in the town centre housing a mix of independent retailers and small businesses. From vintage clothing to artisan food, the Buttermarket is a hub for independent traders.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="info-card">
            <h3>High Street &amp; Beyond</h3>
            <p>Newark's high street blends familiar names with independent shops. Antiques dealers, bookshops, craft suppliers, and specialist food shops give the town centre its distinctive character. The antiques and collectables quarter along Castlegate is a treasure trove.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

