            <h2>Food &amp; Drink</h2>
            <p>Newark punches above its weight when it comes to eating and drinking. The town has an impressive range of restaurants, gastropubs, cafés, and takeaways to suit all tastes and budgets.</p>
            <p>The Market Square is ringed by historic pubs — the White Hart and the Clinton Arms among them — while the Castle Barge offers the unique experience of dining on a floating pub on the River Trent. Independent coffee shops have flourished in recent years, and the market itself offers excellent street food on trading days.</p>
            <p>Newark also has a proud brewing heritage. The town was once home to several breweries, and real ale remains popular in the town's many traditional pubs.</p>
